# Build-context .dockerignore for the grace2-qgis worker image.
#
# UNLIKE the sfincs/modflow/swmm worker images (which build from the REPO ROOT
# and rely on the root /.dockerignore), this image builds with THIS directory as
# its own build context -- see the Dockerfile header:
#     docker build -t grace2-qgis:ltr services/workers/qgis
# So the relevant hygiene boundary is local to services/workers/qgis/.
#
# The Dockerfile COPYs nothing from the context today (it only FROM + apt + a
# qgis_process enable), so the upload is already tiny. This file keeps it that
# way: it guarantees that any future scratch / cache / editor / OS cruft that
# lands in this directory NEVER inflates the tarball sent to the daemon and
# NEVER leaks into an image layer if a later revision adds a COPY. Conservative
# by design -- it excludes only non-runtime cruft, so the built image stays
# byte-identical to a build run in a clean checkout.

# Version control + IDE
.git
.gitignore
.github
.vscode
.idea

# Python build/test caches + venvs (this image installs no Python project)
**/__pycache__
**/*.pyc
**/*.pyo
**/.pytest_cache
**/.mypy_cache
**/.ruff_cache
**/.tox
**/*.egg-info
**/.venv
**/venv
.coverage
**/htmlcov

# Local env + secrets (must never enter a layer)
**/.env
**/.env.*
**/*.local

# Local spike / scratch output
**/_spike_out

# Docs / notes that are not runtime artifacts
**/*.md

# OS cruft
**/.DS_Store
**/Thumbs.db
